## Streaming Large Uploads in ASP.NET Core 8 Minimal API

`IFormFile` buffers the entire request body into memory—that's why it OOMs on large files. Instead, read the multipart stream section-by-section and write directly to disk.

### Key changes needed:

**1. Disable request size limits**

```csharp
// Program.cs
builder.WebApplication.MapPost("/upload", HandleUpload)
    .DisableAntiforgery()
    .WithMetadata(new DisableRequestSizeLimitAttribute());

// Also in Program.cs or appsettings:
builder.Services.Configure<KestrelServerOptions>(o =>
{
    o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024; // 2 GB
});

// If using IIS/IIS Express, also set in web.config:
// <requestLimits maxAllowedContentLength="2147483648" />
```

**2. Stream to disk using `MultipartReader`**

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities;
using Microsoft.Net.Http.Headers;

static async Task<IResult> HandleUpload(HttpRequest request)
{
    if (!request.HasFormContentType ||
        !MediaTypeHeaderValue.TryParse(request.ContentType, out var mt) ||
        string.IsNullOrEmpty(mt.Boundary.Value))
    {
        return Results.BadRequest("Expected a multipart request.");
    }

    var boundary = HeaderUtilities.RemoveQuotes(mt.Boundary.Value).Value!;
    var reader = new MultipartReader(boundary, request.Body);

    MultipartSection? section;
    while ((section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync()) != null)
    {
        if (!ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(
                section.ContentDisposition, out var cd) ||
            !cd.IsFileDisposition())
        {
            continue; // skip non-file fields
        }

        var trustedName = Path.GetRandomFileName(); // never trust client name
        var savePath = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads", trustedName);

        await using var targetStream = File.Create(savePath);
        await section.Body.CopyToAsync(targetStream);
    }

    return Results.Ok("Upload complete.");
}
```

### Why this works

| | `IFormFile` | `MultipartReader` |
|---|---|---|
| Memory | Entire file buffered | Only the read buffer (~80 KB) |
| Max practical size | ~few hundred MB | Limited only by disk |
| Binding model | Model-bound | Manual parsing |

### Don't forget

- **Disable `[FromForm]` binding** — if the framework sees a form content-type and tries to model-bind, it buffers everything. The endpoint should take `HttpRequest` directly.
- **Set `MultipartBodyLengthLimit`** if using `FormOptions`:
  ```csharp
  builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(o =>
  {
      o.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = long.MaxValue;
  });
  ```
- **Validate content** (file type, max size, virus scan) *as you stream* or immediately after, before moving the temp file to its final location.
